1H Pass 2D Pass 2H Pass 3H Pass 4C Pass 4D Pass 4NT Pass 5H Pass 6H Pass Pass Pass
{How do you respond with this nice hand?
With 16+ points and 3 \Hs, you will insist on a \H game at a minimum. But there is no need to start making jump bids, so start with a simple 2\D bid.  This is natural and game forcing.  North rebids 2\H to show a 6-card suit.  What do you rebid now?
Now you say 3\H to set the trump suit, and show slam interest.  At this point North also shows slam interest, making a control-showing bid of 4\C. Do you cooperate? 
Yes, you have an easy, 4\D bid, showing the \DA.
North has heard enough. He bids 4NT, a keycard request using 1430. 

When partner hears about your two keycards without the trump queen, he bids the slam.}

