1S 2D 2H Pass 2S Pass Pass Pass
{South opens 1\S. West overcalls 2\d.  
After West's 2\D overcall both South and North know that the 2/1 Game Force in no longer on. North can therefore bid 2\H, showing at least 11 points. This bid is forcing on South for 1 round, but not forcing to game.
South next rebids his \Ss, promising a 6-card suit, but also indicating a minimum strength hand. Since the Game Force is not on, South would have to make a jump bid to show extra strength.  

You have nothing further to say so the partnership arrives in a safe contract.}

